Package gov.nasa.gsfc.spdf.ssc

Class SatelliteCache

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.nasa.gsfc.spdf.ssc.SatelliteCache
  • public class SatelliteCache
extends java.lang.Object
    This class implements a cache of SSC satellite information which is refreshed periodically. While this class' internal references to the cached information are updated in a thread safe mannor, this class provides no guarentee about concurrent access to the information returned by get().
    Author:
    B. Harris
    See Also:
    PeriodicRefreshedCache

      • get

        public java.util.TreeMap<java.lang.String,​SpaseObservatoryDescription> get()
        Gets a periodicly refreshed cache of SSC satellite metadata. The Map of metadata should be regarded as read-only and only supporting concurrent get operations. The reference returned changes as the cache is refreshed so it is necessary to repeatedly call this method to get the lastest information.
        Returns:
        a Map of SSC satellite metadata or null. It is likely to be null initially before the first successful update has completed.

      • getETag

        public int getETag()
        Produces a weak entity tag hash value for the cached satellites.
        Returns:
        a hash value for the given satellites.
